<TITLE> Youth shot dead in city </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 31 (bdnews24.com)  Unidentified gunmen shot dead a young man after calling him out of his home at Rampura in the city on Wednesday morning, relatives said. The dead was identified as Saiful Islam Sikdar, 30,. He was working as a contractor of the Grameen Paribahan. Dulal, brother of the deceased, said some people called his brother out of their house at 8am, took him behind the old Khilgaon police post, shot him on the head, and fled. He could not confirm why his brother was killed, but he suspected the miscreants might be known to his brother. Assistant sub-inspector of Khilgaon police Saiful Islam told bdnews24.com that it could not be immediately known why Sikdar was killed as none dared to disclose the terrorists' names in fear of reprisal. Islam said police investigation was going on. Personal feud might have caused Islam's murder, police suspected. A murder case has been lodged with Khilgaon police. bdnew
